Aug 12 (Reuters) - The following financial services industry appointments were announced on Tuesday. To inform us of other job changes, email moves@thomsonreuters.com.

BLACKROCK INC <BLK.N> Top Canadian finance ministry official Jean Boivin will join the London office of BlackRock Inc <BLK.N>, the world's largest money manager, the firm said on Monday. Boivin, seen as a contender to head the Bank of Canada one day, is the second most powerful official at the ministry. Boivin will start work as deputy chief investment strategist at the BlackRock Investment Institute on Sept. 15. [ID:nL2N0QH1MB]  NEW CORE CAPITAL MANAGEMENT